"{\"uid\": \"si.com-high-school-california-2024-02-15-orange-lutherans-brenda-villa-4-time-olympian-talks-growth-of-water-polo-on-cif-southern-section-sitdown\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Brenda Villa's story is fascinating.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 36, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brenda_Villa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brenda Villa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brenda_Villa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brenda_Villa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From growing up in the City of Commerce to playing boys water polo at Bell Gardens High, Villa says, \\\"... water polo found me.\\\"\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was a\\u00c2\\u00a04-time 1st team All-League selection, 4-time 1st team All-CIF selection, and 4-time All-American at Bell Gardens ... and that was just the beginning.\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"score\": 0.9999999983624548, \"rank\": 1.6347153098337436e-09, \"text\": \"All-American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\"}, {\"begin\": 278, \"end\": 290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bell_Gardens,_California\", \"score\": 0.9554950730070675, \"rank\": 0.0465766185374927, \"text\": \"Bell Gardens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bell_Gardens,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bell_Gardens,_California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Villa ended up playing at Stanford where she won the\\u00c2\\u00a0Peter J. Cutino Award\\u00c2\\u00a0in 2002, which is like the Heisman Trophy in college water polo.\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 0.9999999996600764, \"rank\": 2.4025104917188436e-10, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}, {\"begin\": 383, \"end\": 388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Pan\", \"score\": 0.9999994920057287, \"rank\": 3.805789615998003e-07, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Pan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Pan\"}, {\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heisman_Trophy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heisman Trophy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heisman_Trophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heisman_Trophy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She then went on to compete for team USA in four Olympics - 2000 Sydney, 2004 Athens, 2008 Beijing and 2012 London.\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 508, \"end\": 511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9956686058013401, \"rank\": 0.004298599812936879, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 531, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997311445348, \"rank\": 1.7303581493986734e-07, \"text\": \"2000 Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7460100033139652, \"rank\": 0.3404567241103039, \"text\": \"2004 Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9893902396613011, \"rank\": 0.01066042462142706, \"text\": \"2008 Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999996699794428, \"rank\": 3.3000144080564485e-07, \"text\": \"2012 London\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was everything you could imagine and more,\\\" Villa said of her Olympic experience.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was at the first (Olympics) ever for women's water polo.\\\"\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Villa won silver, bronze, silver and gold in the four Olympics, respectively.\\u00c2  Villa has won four Olympic medals, four World Championship medals, three Pan American Games medals, eight FINA World League medals and one FINA World Cup.\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"score\": 0.9984459507388023, \"rank\": 0.0013421396071282784, \"text\": \"Pan American Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA_Water_Polo_World_League\", \"score\": 0.99564512427351, \"rank\": 0.004373919414582671, \"text\": \"World League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA_Water_Polo_World_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA_Water_Polo_World_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of those 20 competitions, Villa won gold in 15 of them, making her\\u00c2\\u00a0the most decorated athlete in the world of women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s water polo.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Villa was named Female Water Polo Player of the Decade for 2000-2009 by the FINA Aquatics World Magazine.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1129, \"end\": 1139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Water_polo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3665491227095008e-16, \"text\": \"Water Polo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Water_polo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Water_polo\"}, {\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.282971461920391e-25, \"text\": \"FINA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\"}, {\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9999994961184616, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Magazine\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_(magazine)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is a leading goalscorer in Olympic water polo history, with 31 goals, and in\\u00c2\\u00a02018, was inducted into the International Swimming Hall of Fame and the USA Water Polo Hall of Fame.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite winning gold in London, Villa says the Sydney games were her favorite.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\"